    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-10-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loring</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-10-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 15, 1889</date>. (Received October
                        28.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I regret to inform you that His Majesty Luiz I,
                    King of Portugal, has after many months of ill health, become entirely
                    prostrated and it is felt that his life is in danger.</p>
                <p>The loss of the King will be great to the Portuguese people. Accomplished,
                    judicious, patriotic, and devoted to his country, he has secured the affection
                    of the community here, and the respect of all associate powers. The anxiety with
                    regard to him is intense.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. B. Loring.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
